definition.value: A person of the same sex/gender (a man living with a man or a woman living with a woman) with whom one shares living quarters.
A person of the "opposite" sex (a man living with a woman or a woman living with a man) with whom one shares living quarters.
Coitus and/or sexual intercourse occurring between a married person and someone other their spouse.
Coitus and/or sexual intercourse practiced by persons who are married to one another.
Coitus and/or sexual intercourse practiced by persons before they are married.
An arrangement where parties, known as partners, agree to cooperate to advance their mutual interests.
An interpersonal relationship between two individuals who live together and share a common domestic life, but are not married (to each other or to anyone else).
A partnership which includes sexual activity between its constituents.
Multiple sexual partnerships which overlap in time.
A sexual relationship, romantic friendship, or passionate attachment between two people without the attached person's significant other knowing.
An affair outside of the context of a marital relationship; cheating.
Note that part of an agreement within nonmonogamous relationships as to what constitutes an affair may differ, with some forms being permitted and others not.
Relationships outside of marriage where an illicit romantic or sexual relationship or a romantic friendship or passionate attachment occurs.
An affair which involves computer-mediated communication such as texting, social media connections, and instant messaging, among other things.
A relationship between persons of the same gender and can take many forms, from romantic and sexual, to non-romantic homosocially-close relationships.

Note that, although "same-gender relationship" and "same-sex relationship" may be used colloquially to refer to sexual and/or romantic same-sex relationships, it is in actuality broader, including platonic same-sex relationships as well.
A non-romantic and non-sexual relationship between persons of the same gender.
A relationship based on mutual romantic love between persons of the same gender.
A relationship involving some kind of sexual intimacy between persons of the same gender.
A relationship between persons of different genders and can take many forms, from romantic and sexual, to non-romantic homosocially-close relationships.
A relationship between two persons who are male.
A relationship between two persons who are female.
A relationship between a person who is male and a person who is female.
A relationship involving some kind of sexual intimacy between persons of different genders.
A relationship based on mutual romantic love between persons of different genders.
A non-romantic and non-sexual relationship between persons of different sex.
A relationship involving some kind of sexual intimacy between at least two people in which at least one person is a lesbian.
A relationship involving some kind of sexual intimacy between at least two people in which at least one person is a gay man.
A relationship involving some kind of sexual intimacy between at least two people in which at least one person is heterosexual.
A friendship between a man and a woman.
A relationship of mutual affection between two women which includes a stronger form of interpersonal bond than an association.
A relationship of mutual affection between two men which includes a stronger form of interpersonal bond than an association.

A physical and emotional relationship between two people who may have casual sex or a near-sexual relationship without necessarily demanding or expecting the extra commitments of a more formal romantic relationship.
Interpersonal relationships which attains some form of internal or external significance (such as a marriage or civil union).
A significant relationship considered to have formally begun with a legal marriage, religious marriage ceremony, or some other cultural equivalent.
A pattern in which a group or groups of organisms are structured in relation to sexual behavior.
A pattern in which a group or groups of animals are structured in relation to sexual behavior.
A pattern in which a group or groups of plants are structured in relation to sexual behavior.
Mating systems as observed in vertebrates.
Mating systems as observed in mammals.
Mating systems as observed in primates.
Mating systems as observed in humans.
a form of relationship or pairing in which an individual has only one partner during their lifetime or, alternately, only one partner at any one time.
An umbrella term for any mating system which is not monogamous.
Any form of multiple mating.
A form of polygamy in which one male has an exclusive relationship with two or more females.
A form of polygamy in which one female has an exclusive relationship with two or more males.
A form of polygamy in which two or more males have an exclusive relationship with two or more females.
A form of mating system in which organisms within the social group mates with any member of another sex classification.
A relationship in which a pair of organisms share a social living arrangement, such as shared use of territory or proximity between the pair).
An exclusive sexual relationship based on observations of sexual interactions.
A relationship where DNA analyses can confirm that a pair of organisms reproduce exclusively with each other.
